[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] Java provides automatic serialization which requires that the object be marked by implementing the `java.io.Serializable` interface.
[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] Implementing the interface marks the class as "okay to serialize", and Java then handles serialization internally.
