[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] The core general serialization mechanism is the `pickle` standard library module, alluding to the database systems term *pickling* to describe data serialization (*unpickling* for *deserializing*).
[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] Pickle uses a simple stack-based virtual machine that records the instructions used to reconstruct the object.
[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] It is a cross-version customizable but unsafe (not secure against erroneous or malicious data) serialization format.
[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] Malformed or maliciously constructed data, may cause the deserializer to import arbitrary modules and instantiate any object.
[src:protobuf-cpp-lib/serialization] The standard library also includes modules serializing to standard data formats: `json` (with built-in support for basic scalar and collection types and able to support arbitrary types via encoding and decoding hooks).
